## Raise the Pull Request

1. Create a new branch: `git checkout -b onboarding/add-user-[your-name]`
2. Commit your changes: `git add . && git commit -m "Add user access: [your name]"`
3. Push to remote: `git push origin onboarding/add-user-[your-name]`
4. Create the PR in GitHub with title: `Add user access: [your name]`

## PR Description Template

Include the following in your PR description:

```
User: [Your Name]
Email: [your-email@hmcts.net]
Team: [Selected Team]
Manager: [Manager Name]

Requesting access to:
- [ ] Non-live tenant
- [ ] Live tenant (approval from manager required)
```

